snippet.title: Best phones
snippet.description: Looking for phones? CNET's reviews of the best phones include photos, video, and user reviews.

snippet.title: Dash (Android)
snippet.description: Dash is a great system for frequent drivers wanting to monitor their gas usage and driving behaviors.

snippet.title: Neato XV-21
snippet.description: The XV-21 is a great all-around robot vacuum and a viable Roomba alternative, but among Neatos, we'll stick with the brainier, similarly priced XV Signature Pro.

snippet.title: Nike FuelBand -- out of gas already?
snippet.description: The sportswear company could be close to ditching its fitness hardware efforts, but don’t sound the death knell for Nike technology. Consider, for one thing, the Apple connection.

snippet.title: Sony SmartWatch 2
snippet.description: With its ability to push Android notifications to your wrist, the Sony SmartWatch 2 is more useful than Samsung’s Galaxy Gear, but the Pebble is still the best smartwatch deal around.

snippet.title: Samsung Gravity Q (T-Mobile)
snippet.description: If you're not opting for a smartphone and you can look past its dated design, the Samsung Gravity Q is your best choice for a T-Mobile keyboard phone.

snippet.title: LG Smart ThinQ 7.3 cu. ft. SteamDryer (gas)
snippet.description: LG's Smart ThinQ appliances have an impressive array of top-of-the-line features. Of course, at $1,599 for an electric unit and $1,699 for the gas model, this dryer comes with a top-of-the-line price tag, too.

snippet.title: Insteon LED Bulb
snippet.description: At just $29.99 per bulb, this automatable light source will fit nicely into existing home automation networks, serving as an appealing alternative to more expensive dimmer modules and smart switches.

snippet.title: Apple: Samsung made 'false statements' during opening argument
snippet.description: Apple asks the judge in a California patent case to let it present previously banned testimony and evidence. Samsung, unsurprisingly, says the motion should be denied.
